1
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:38,767
<i> Why is it like that, Alice?</i>

2
00:00:38,900 --> 00:00:41,900
<i> All I remember are our fights.</i>

3
00:00:42,033 --> 00:00:44,433
<i>Because that's what you
pretty much did to her.</i>

4
00:00:44,567 --> 00:00:47,433
<i>If any of you were gone,
I'd feel the same.</i>

5
00:00:47,567 --> 00:00:49,667
<i>You all hold the same
place in my heart.</i>

6
00:00:49,800 --> 00:00:51,233
<i> Dear, why are you sad?</i>

7
00:00:51,367 --> 00:00:53,733
<i> Aren't you happy to see me?</i>

8
00:00:53,867 --> 00:00:55,400
<i> Please forgive me.</i>

9
00:00:55,533 --> 00:00:56,667
<i> Goodbye.</i>

10
00:00:56,800 --> 00:00:59,833
<i>Which one of you
is Miss Coleen Ruiz Cruz?</i>

11
00:00:59,967 --> 00:01:01,267
<i> I chased her.</i>

12
00:01:01,400 --> 00:01:03,933
<i> We were struggling until...</i>

13
00:01:04,067 --> 00:01:06,833
<i> she got out of my grip.</i>

14
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:09,933
<i> I couldn't save Jessica.</i>

15
00:01:17,067 --> 00:01:19,100
She wanted Jessica
out of her life.

16
00:01:20,133 --> 00:01:21,267
So she pushed her.

17
00:01:23,033 --> 00:01:27,833
Attorney, how many times
did Coleen hurt Jessica?

18
00:01:29,133 --> 00:01:30,367
My child put up with it.

19
00:01:31,433 --> 00:01:32,500
I wouldn't even have known

20
00:01:32,633 --> 00:01:34,867
if she hadn't come back
covered in cuts and bruises.

21
00:01:36,333 --> 00:01:38,967
Yes, we can argue motive.

22
00:01:39,533 --> 00:01:40,833
But still...

23
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:42,200
What?

24
00:01:42,333 --> 00:01:43,900
Still no evidence?

25
00:01:44,033 --> 00:01:45,367
Darn that evidence!

26
00:01:45,500 --> 00:01:46,700
Evidence my ass!

27
00:01:46,833 --> 00:01:48,300
I have a video of Coleen.

28
00:01:48,433 --> 00:01:50,567
She says she doesn't
like Jessica.

29
00:01:50,700 --> 00:01:51,333
There.

30
00:01:52,333 --> 00:01:53,600
Isn't that enough?

31
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:57,800
Mrs. Cruz, you recorded
that illegally.

32
00:01:58,767 --> 00:01:59,933
It's not admissible.

33
00:02:00,067 --> 00:02:01,300
You know that.

34
00:02:02,967 --> 00:02:04,600
Mrs. Cruz, maybe
don't drink yet.

35
00:02:04,733 --> 00:02:05,967
Eat something first.

36
00:02:06,833 --> 00:02:07,767
I don't feel like it.

37
00:02:15,767 --> 00:02:16,500
Okay, fine.

38
00:02:16,633 --> 00:02:17,833
Go on, eat it.

39
00:02:26,100 --> 00:02:27,600
We have nothing to worry about.

40
00:02:28,633 --> 00:02:31,167
The investigation is still
focused on finding the driver

41
00:02:31,300 --> 00:02:32,500
who hit Jessica.

42
00:02:33,333 --> 00:02:37,033
They just want to clarify
what happened

43
00:02:37,500 --> 00:02:40,233
and why it led
to Jessica's death.

44
00:02:41,100 --> 00:02:42,033
Thank you, Attorney.

45
00:02:44,533 --> 00:02:46,600
I hope the person who hit
my sister feels guilty.

46
00:02:48,033 --> 00:02:49,033
I hope he turns himself in.

47
00:02:51,267 --> 00:02:53,400
But Hazel still
won't stop, Jeff.

48
00:02:54,333 --> 00:02:57,067
She's insisting I'm the one
who killed Jessica.

49
00:02:57,867 --> 00:02:59,033
She has to prove that.

50
00:02:59,700 --> 00:03:01,767
The burden of proof
is on her, okay?

51
00:03:02,533 --> 00:03:08,900
And so far, there's no witness
to prove you pushed Jessica.

52
00:03:09,033 --> 00:03:15,133
I'm telling you, sweetheart,
Hazel can't change the truth.

53
00:03:24,233 --> 00:03:25,000
Okay.

54
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:28,133
Okay, thank you.

55
00:03:32,600 --> 00:03:34,133
That was my contact
at the police station.

56
00:03:35,467 --> 00:03:37,200
They've already sent
Coleen home.

57
00:03:38,367 --> 00:03:39,067
What?

58
00:03:40,067 --> 00:03:41,033
Why?

59
00:03:42,867 --> 00:03:45,267
She told them
she didn't push Jessica.

60
00:03:45,933 --> 00:03:47,167
She's such a liar.

61
00:03:48,167 --> 00:03:50,133
Mrs. Cruz, there's no other
witness

62
00:03:50,267 --> 00:03:51,767
to contradict her statement.

63
00:03:53,633 --> 00:03:55,533
If I were you, I wouldn't
chase Coleen down.

64
00:03:55,700 --> 00:04:00,433
We can't file charges
without sufficient evidence.

65
00:04:00,833 --> 00:04:04,200
Find evidence against
that woman, Attorney.

66
00:04:05,067 --> 00:04:06,733
We won't find anything

67
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:11,633
if the person you want to charge
is telling the truth.

68
00:04:12,767 --> 00:04:15,133
You believe that liar?

69
00:04:15,800 --> 00:04:18,300
Or are you just too lazy to look
for proof, Attorney?

70
00:04:18,900 --> 00:04:20,933
Fine, if you won't, I will.

71
00:04:21,700 --> 00:04:23,967
I'll make sure I dig
something up.

72
00:04:24,867 --> 00:04:26,533
Whatever you plan to do...

73
00:04:28,300 --> 00:04:31,933
please, don't break the law.

74
00:04:32,567 --> 00:04:34,267
<i> Don't do anything reckless.</i>

75
00:04:34,400 --> 00:04:37,333
Don't interfere with my plan,
Attorney.

76
00:04:37,467 --> 00:04:39,300
I have one thing I want.

77
00:04:39,433 --> 00:04:41,500
To make whoever killed
my child pay.

78
00:04:49,333 --> 00:04:51,067
A police officer spoke
with Coleen?

79
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:53,833
Wasn't my godchild
traumatized, Bro?

80
00:04:53,967 --> 00:04:55,800
She brought up
what happened again.

81
00:04:55,933 --> 00:04:58,367
We weren't able to talk.

82
00:04:58,500 --> 00:05:00,700
When she arrived, she just
went straight to her room.

83
00:05:01,500 --> 00:05:02,767
<i> Paz.</i>

84
00:05:02,900 --> 00:05:05,167
Yeah, I'm about to leave.

85
00:05:05,300 --> 00:05:06,233
Just a minute.

86
00:05:06,367 --> 00:05:07,300
I'll see you.

87
00:05:07,433 --> 00:05:08,600
Bye.

88
00:05:08,733 --> 00:05:09,600
- Felma.
- Abel.

89
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:11,300
How's Coleen?

90
00:05:12,400 --> 00:05:13,667
She's resting.

91
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:17,367
I had Jeffrey and Andrea
keep an eye on her.

92
00:05:17,500 --> 00:05:19,000
I've got to go.

93
00:05:19,133 --> 00:05:20,900
I have a meeting
at Konsumo Mart.

94
00:05:22,133 --> 00:05:23,967
- All right, take care.
- You, too.

95
00:05:28,400 --> 00:05:30,967
That driver was an animal!

96
00:05:31,100 --> 00:05:34,100
Because of him,
Jessica's gone.

97
00:05:34,267 --> 00:05:35,833
And look at Coleen.

98
00:05:36,500 --> 00:05:37,600
She can't find peace.

99
00:05:37,733 --> 00:05:39,667
She's scared that she'll be
blamed for what happened.

100
00:05:40,567 --> 00:05:46,700
But you said Coleen was okay,
according to Atty. Yeban.

101
00:05:46,833 --> 00:05:50,933
Yeah, but Hazel's pushing hard.

102
00:05:51,067 --> 00:05:53,300
She insists Coleen is to blame.

103
00:05:53,433 --> 00:05:55,367
You know that woman.

104
00:05:55,500 --> 00:05:58,133
She'll do anything to pin it
on my child.

105
00:06:04,067 --> 00:06:04,933
<i> What?</i>

106
00:06:05,633 --> 00:06:07,900
You're really going
to expose Coleen?

107
00:06:08,800 --> 00:06:09,433
Come on, friend.

108
00:06:09,567 --> 00:06:10,900
You don't even have evidence.

109
00:06:12,933 --> 00:06:13,833
We'll get there.

110
00:06:15,467 --> 00:06:17,500
What I need now
is perception.

111
00:06:19,933 --> 00:06:23,567
I need to win
the people's sympathy.

112
00:06:25,167 --> 00:06:26,833
So they'll believe

113
00:06:26,967 --> 00:06:28,900
that it wasn't just
the hit-and-run driver

114
00:06:29,033 --> 00:06:31,933
who killed Jessica,
but also the one who pushed her.

115
00:06:33,700 --> 00:06:35,667
Once I gain
the public's sympathy,

116
00:06:36,833 --> 00:06:38,133
someone might come forward.

117
00:06:39,667 --> 00:06:44,800
Someone who'll say they saw
Coleen push Jessica.

118
00:06:46,867 --> 00:06:50,467
Friend, can't you just grieve
for Jessica first?

119
00:06:50,600 --> 00:06:53,700
Stop thinking only about
putting Coleen in jail.

120
00:06:57,133 --> 00:06:58,967
This is my way of grieving.

121
00:07:00,667 --> 00:07:03,167
I mourned my daughter
the moment she died.

122
00:07:04,067 --> 00:07:06,467
And I'm still mourning her now.

123
00:07:07,467 --> 00:07:08,367
If only you knew...

124
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:11,433
I still cry for her
every single day.

125
00:07:13,267 --> 00:07:15,367
But I can't just keep crying.

126
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:20,900
I won't stop until
Jessica's death gets justice.

127
00:07:22,067 --> 00:07:24,967
Whoever killed her must pay.

128
00:07:28,300 --> 00:07:30,667
Have you called Karla Talakera?

129
00:07:31,433 --> 00:07:34,367
I did, but she's out
of the country.

130
00:07:35,233 --> 00:07:38,800
She's referred me
to Xander Yamson,

131
00:07:38,933 --> 00:07:42,533
a.k.a. Detective XY.

132
00:07:42,667 --> 00:07:46,133
He's an influencer obsessed
with solving crimes.

133
00:07:46,267 --> 00:07:47,867
He's got nearly a million
followers.

134
00:07:49,867 --> 00:07:50,567
Perfect.

135
00:07:51,067 --> 00:07:52,133
Can you call him?

136
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:55,267
Ask if he's available later.

137
00:07:55,900 --> 00:07:57,467
All right.

138
00:08:02,500 --> 00:08:05,667
Hazel won't succeed.

139
00:08:06,467 --> 00:08:09,500
If anyone's to blame
for Jessica's death,

140
00:08:09,633 --> 00:08:12,367
it's that bastard who hit her.

141
00:08:12,967 --> 00:08:14,300
That damn fool.

142
00:08:14,433 --> 00:08:15,833
You were always
so careful with Jessica.

143
00:08:15,967 --> 00:08:17,800
You loved that goddaughter
of mine so much.

144
00:08:18,433 --> 00:08:20,433
You raised her since
she was a baby.

145
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:22,500
You bathed her,
changed her diaper,

146
00:08:22,633 --> 00:08:24,000
and bottle-fed her.

147
00:08:25,367 --> 00:08:26,933
You did everything for her, Bro.

148
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:31,000
Jessica filled
the emptiness I felt

149
00:08:31,133 --> 00:08:33,233
for Jeffrey, Andrea,
and even Coleen.

150
00:08:35,033 --> 00:08:38,967
This was my chance to love them
all at once,

151
00:08:39,100 --> 00:08:40,200
to have them together.

152
00:08:41,933 --> 00:08:43,633
How did it end up like this?

153
00:08:44,267 --> 00:08:47,233
This was supposed to be the time

154
00:08:47,367 --> 00:08:48,467
your children would
all be together.

155
00:08:49,267 --> 00:08:53,867
And then some heartless
idiot took Jessica away.

156
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:56,200
That animal smashed into her.

157
00:08:56,367 --> 00:08:59,133
If they catch that bastard,
let me hit him one time.

158
00:09:00,233 --> 00:09:02,100
I'll smash his jaw.

159
00:09:09,133 --> 00:09:10,400
What's wrong, Alice?

160
00:09:12,167 --> 00:09:14,033
Can you not do this?

161
00:09:14,733 --> 00:09:16,133
I feel bad for Coleen.

162
00:09:19,033 --> 00:09:20,067
What about my child?

163
00:09:21,267 --> 00:09:22,433
Do you honestly believe

164
00:09:22,567 --> 00:09:24,567
- she pushed Jessica?
- Yes.

165
00:09:25,700 --> 00:09:27,800
That's why I'm so frustrated
there's no witness.

166
00:09:30,833 --> 00:09:33,233
Alice, I owe Jessica
a great deal.

167
00:09:34,700 --> 00:09:37,133
I want justice for her death.

168
00:09:39,233 --> 00:09:42,400
If nothing else,
let me make that right.

169
00:09:54,800 --> 00:09:56,033
Thank you.

170
00:09:58,633 --> 00:09:59,400
No problem.

171
00:09:59,533 --> 00:10:01,200
Ma'am, we're live right now.

172
00:10:01,367 --> 00:10:04,767
2,451 viewers
and counting.

173
00:10:04,900 --> 00:10:09,433
I've already told them the
background of tonight's topic.

174
00:10:09,567 --> 00:10:10,100
Please, Ma'am.

175
00:10:10,233 --> 00:10:11,333
Have a seat here.

176
00:10:12,700 --> 00:10:13,267
Over here.

177
00:10:18,467 --> 00:10:19,167
Make sure you're on camera.

178
00:10:27,833 --> 00:10:28,900
Hello, XY family.

179
00:10:29,033 --> 00:10:30,167
I'm back.

180
00:10:30,300 --> 00:10:34,033
Detective XY, your unofficial
online investigator

181
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:35,967
and digital vigilante.

182
00:10:36,100 --> 00:10:41,100
Guys, my guest tonight
is Mrs. Hazel Cruz,

183
00:10:41,933 --> 00:10:45,667
the mother of Jessica,
the hit-and-run victim

184
00:10:45,800 --> 00:10:47,367
who broke everyone's hearts.

185
00:10:47,500 --> 00:10:50,533
Ma'am, welcome to my channel.

186
00:10:50,667 --> 00:10:53,500
So, Ma'am, could you tell us
live, for the viewers,

187
00:10:53,633 --> 00:10:57,300
what made you contact me
tonight?

188
00:11:09,933 --> 00:11:11,200
This is Jessica...

189
00:11:13,500 --> 00:11:14,667
my daughter.

190
00:11:14,800 --> 00:11:15,700
She was kind.

191
00:11:19,300 --> 00:11:20,333
Affectionate.

192
00:11:22,167 --> 00:11:23,200
A loving child.

193
00:11:25,367 --> 00:11:29,867
I love looking at her face
because she's beautiful.

194
00:11:34,767 --> 00:11:41,733
But on the night of her wake,
her casket was closed because...

195
00:11:43,800 --> 00:11:45,667
her face was destroyed.

196
00:11:46,333 --> 00:11:47,133
Oh my God.

197
00:11:51,333 --> 00:11:56,600
I'm pleading with the driver
who hit my daughter.

198
00:12:00,367 --> 00:12:01,400
He ran away.

199
00:12:02,700 --> 00:12:04,267
<i> He's hiding now.</i>

200
00:12:06,067 --> 00:12:07,500
Please, surrender yourself.

201
00:12:09,933 --> 00:12:11,800
Be accountable for what you did
to my child.

202
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:17,867
And besides the driver,

203
00:12:21,333 --> 00:12:22,600
I also want to appeal...

204
00:12:26,767 --> 00:12:31,733
I also want to appeal to the
person who pushed Jessica.

205
00:12:33,267 --> 00:12:34,433
Admit it.

206
00:12:36,433 --> 00:12:38,033
Admit what you did.

207
00:12:40,067 --> 00:12:41,533
Take responsibility.

208
00:12:42,700 --> 00:12:44,867
Wait, someone pushed
your daughter?

209
00:12:45,933 --> 00:12:46,933
Yes.

210
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:49,300
And the worst part is,

211
00:12:51,033 --> 00:12:52,633
the person who pushed Jessica...

212
00:12:55,067 --> 00:12:56,100
was someone close to her.

213
00:12:59,400 --> 00:13:00,800
Someone close to her heart.

214
00:13:02,500 --> 00:13:04,700
Is it okay for the viewers
to know who that is?

215
00:13:09,933 --> 00:13:13,100
Detective XY, I'm sorry.

216
00:13:14,367 --> 00:13:19,800
My lawyer told me
not to mention names.

217
00:13:20,133 --> 00:13:24,067
He said I could be sued
because there's no evidence yet.

218
00:13:25,567 --> 00:13:29,867
But as a parent,
I can't just stay quiet.

219
00:13:33,867 --> 00:13:36,067
No matter what happens,
she won't confess.

220
00:13:36,867 --> 00:13:40,267
Even her mother
and her siblings.

221
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:42,233
They're all protecting her.

222
00:13:43,567 --> 00:13:44,600
Her?

223
00:13:45,300 --> 00:13:48,133
So, it was a woman who pushed
your daughter?

224
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:51,767
Yes.

225
00:13:52,800 --> 00:13:53,867
What makes it worse...

226
00:13:56,167 --> 00:13:59,167
is that the CCTV didn't catch
the actual push.

227
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:00,967
That's it.

228
00:14:01,700 --> 00:14:03,967
That's how easy it is
to escape responsibility.

229
00:14:06,033 --> 00:14:10,567
Sometimes you can't get justice
because one angle is missing.

230
00:14:13,033 --> 00:14:16,000
Please, I'm begging you.

231
00:14:17,700 --> 00:14:24,567
If any of you were
at Southcrest Premier Hospital

232
00:14:24,700 --> 00:14:28,633
when my daughter's accident
happened,

233
00:14:28,800 --> 00:14:36,933
if any of you saw someone push
Jessica, please help me.

234
00:14:37,067 --> 00:14:46,267
Or if you know someone
who saw it happen,

235
00:14:46,400 --> 00:14:48,600
<i> please share this video.</i>

236
00:14:48,733 --> 00:14:49,633
<i> Please.</i>

237
00:14:50,233 --> 00:14:54,467
<i>Help me get justice
for my daughter's death.</i>

238
00:14:59,333 --> 00:15:02,433
All right, we're getting
a lot of comments.

239
00:15:02,600 --> 00:15:04,733
Live comment from Anne Lim

240
00:15:04,867 --> 00:15:07,067
"Is that Mrs. Cruz
the same woman

241
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:08,667
Karla Talakera interviewed
before?

242
00:15:08,800 --> 00:15:14,700
<i>The wife of the FMP owner's
lover? #JusticeForJessica"</i>

243
00:15:14,833 --> 00:15:17,133
Andrew 1673 says

244
00:15:17,267 --> 00:15:21,333
"Yeah, Felma Ruiz? #Felmalandi.

245
00:15:21,467 --> 00:15:24,133
Could she be the one
who pushed Jessica?"

246
00:15:24,267 --> 00:15:25,667
<i>There are already
so many comments, Ma'am.</i>

247
00:15:25,800 --> 00:15:28,700
Oh, here's another one...

248
00:15:28,833 --> 00:15:32,067
"I was at SPH
when this happened.

249
00:15:32,200 --> 00:15:35,300
Jessica was with someone
her age before she got hit.

250
00:15:35,467 --> 00:15:38,100
Not sure if she was
pushed, though."

251
00:15:38,233 --> 00:15:39,533
It's going viral.

252
00:15:40,467 --> 00:15:41,567
So many people are sharing it.

253
00:15:42,233 --> 00:15:43,600
Everyone's angry. Look, Dad.

254
00:15:43,733 --> 00:15:45,833
And tons of people
are mentioning Coleen's name.

255
00:15:48,767 --> 00:15:50,000
Gosh!

256
00:15:50,133 --> 00:15:51,033
They're really
calling her out now.

257
00:15:51,167 --> 00:15:52,800
Naming names.

258
00:15:52,933 --> 00:15:56,233
Netizens really know
how to dig up information.

259
00:15:57,733 --> 00:15:59,400
<i> Coleen's getting bashed.</i>

260
00:15:59,533 --> 00:16:01,000
I feel bad for my goddaughter.

261
00:16:02,200 --> 00:16:04,033
That's the problem
with social media.

262
00:16:04,767 --> 00:16:06,600
People dig too fast.

263
00:16:07,133 --> 00:16:07,933
They judge too fast!

264
00:16:09,267 --> 00:16:12,600
Most of them believe
fake news so easily.

265
00:16:12,733 --> 00:16:15,633
No wonder so many end up
with mental health issues.

266
00:16:17,067 --> 00:16:19,700
Just ignore them, okay?

267
00:16:19,833 --> 00:16:22,133
And no one should respond.

268
00:16:22,267 --> 00:16:24,267
Your sister doesn't need
to know this.

269
00:16:24,400 --> 00:16:26,167
She might not handle it.

270
00:16:26,300 --> 00:16:28,800
Hazel really is a monster.

271
00:16:28,933 --> 00:16:31,400
<i> Again, this is Detective XY,</i>

272
00:16:31,533 --> 00:16:33,633
<i>your unofficial online
investigator</i>

273
00:16:33,767 --> 00:16:35,167
<i> and digital vigilante.</i>

274
00:16:46,033 --> 00:16:47,333
Yeah, Rona.

275
00:16:47,467 --> 00:16:50,233
I'm sorry, I won't be able
to come in for now.

276
00:16:50,367 --> 00:16:52,500
There are just
too many problems at home.

277
00:16:54,133 --> 00:16:55,200
Yeah, I'm okay.

278
00:16:55,333 --> 00:16:56,100
Don't worry.

279
00:16:57,667 --> 00:16:59,300
Thanks for calling, though.

280
00:17:01,633 --> 00:17:02,767
<i> Knock, knock!</i>

281
00:17:02,900 --> 00:17:03,767
Coleen!

282
00:17:04,167 --> 00:17:04,767
Where's your sister?

283
00:17:07,733 --> 00:17:08,333
Coleen.

284
00:17:16,600 --> 00:17:23,733
Back in college, there was
a frat war outside our school.

285
00:17:25,400 --> 00:17:26,800
It was already late.

286
00:17:26,933 --> 00:17:28,133
Not many people around.

287
00:17:29,500 --> 00:17:30,800
Someone got shot.

288
00:17:31,833 --> 00:17:32,433
Dead.

289
00:17:33,233 --> 00:17:34,133
Everyone ran.

290
00:17:34,267 --> 00:17:35,467
I froze.

291
00:17:35,600 --> 00:17:37,467
I was scared. I couldn't run.

292
00:17:38,500 --> 00:17:39,700
I got blamed.

293
00:17:42,967 --> 00:17:43,567
Yes.

294
00:17:45,167 --> 00:17:46,633
Someone even pointed at me.

295
00:17:47,667 --> 00:17:49,133
But I was innocent.

296
00:17:49,900 --> 00:17:52,333
I just told the truth
that I happened to be there.

297
00:17:53,500 --> 00:17:54,500
That's all I did.

298
00:17:55,467 --> 00:17:56,933
I stood by the truth.

299
00:17:58,200 --> 00:17:59,367
That's all you have to do,
Coleen.

300
00:18:01,300 --> 00:18:03,033
No matter how hard
they press you,

301
00:18:03,733 --> 00:18:05,633
the truth will always come out.

302
00:18:06,700 --> 00:18:07,633
Okay?

303
00:18:12,700 --> 00:18:14,200
Thank you.

304
00:18:22,933 --> 00:18:23,867
Sweetie.

305
00:18:26,167 --> 00:18:27,200
Why?

306
00:18:31,467 --> 00:18:34,467
Rona says I'm going viral.

307
00:18:35,167 --> 00:18:36,433
She even sent a link.

308
00:18:37,867 --> 00:18:38,567
Don't click it.

309
00:18:38,700 --> 00:18:39,433
- Andrea!
- Coleen!

310
00:18:39,567 --> 00:18:40,700
- Give it to me!
- Coleen, please!

311
00:18:40,833 --> 00:18:42,233
- Andrea!
- Don't click it!

312
00:18:42,367 --> 00:18:43,400
Andrea!

313
00:18:46,167 --> 00:18:49,000
<i>No matter what happens,
she won't confess.</i>

314
00:18:49,133 --> 00:18:52,500
<i> Even her mother and siblings.</i>

315
00:18:52,633 --> 00:18:54,600
<i> They're all protecting her.</i>

316
00:18:56,033 --> 00:18:57,100
<i> Her?</i>

317
00:18:57,233 --> 00:18:58,167
<i> So...</i>

318
00:18:58,300 --> 00:18:59,800
<i>it was a woman who
pushed your daughter?</i>

319
00:18:59,933 --> 00:19:01,600
There are so many...

320
00:19:01,733 --> 00:19:04,300
so many hate comments.

321
00:19:04,433 --> 00:19:05,633
So many bashers.

322
00:19:07,767 --> 00:19:09,800
Sweetie, that's enough.

323
00:19:09,933 --> 00:19:12,567
Andrea, they really believe
I pushed Jessica.

324
00:19:13,833 --> 00:19:15,600
I can't go out anymore.

325
00:19:15,733 --> 00:19:17,600
They see me as a killer.

326
00:19:22,433 --> 00:19:25,267
They really believe
I pushed Jessica.

327
00:19:26,300 --> 00:19:28,167
I can't get out anymore.

328
00:19:28,300 --> 00:19:29,900
They see me as a killer.

329
00:19:37,033 --> 00:19:38,600
I understand you.

330
00:19:40,033 --> 00:19:41,333
But calm down.

331
00:19:42,667 --> 00:19:44,000
I've been through that too.

332
00:19:45,100 --> 00:19:48,267
Being bashed even when
you've done nothing wrong.

333
00:19:50,300 --> 00:19:52,567
But, sweetie, don't mind them.

334
00:19:52,700 --> 00:19:54,100
Don't let it affect you.

335
00:19:54,800 --> 00:19:57,900
What happened to you
was just a scamming issue.

336
00:20:00,167 --> 00:20:04,867
But with me,
everyone thinks I'm a killer.

337
00:20:06,133 --> 00:20:09,167
Andrea, I never wanted what
happened to Jessica.

338
00:20:10,267 --> 00:20:13,100
I never wanted her to be gone.

339
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:19,600
Sweetie, we know the truth.

340
00:20:22,167 --> 00:20:23,500
We know the truth, right?

341
00:20:29,400 --> 00:20:30,167
That's enough.

342
00:20:30,300 --> 00:20:31,100
Enough.

343
00:20:42,567 --> 00:20:44,367
Coleen refuses to come down.

344
00:20:44,500 --> 00:20:45,500
She won't eat.

345
00:20:46,933 --> 00:20:49,167
Jeff, Abel, help me go upstairs.

346
00:20:49,300 --> 00:20:50,667
I need to talk to her.

347
00:20:50,800 --> 00:20:51,367
Let's go.

348
00:20:51,500 --> 00:20:52,567
Manuel, don't.

349
00:20:53,333 --> 00:20:55,033
She doesn't want anyone
talking to her.

350
00:20:55,167 --> 00:20:56,300
Let's just give her time.

351
00:20:57,300 --> 00:20:58,233
Mom...

352
00:20:59,367 --> 00:21:02,233
Coleen told me she doesn't want

353
00:21:02,367 --> 00:21:04,767
to go back to school anymore,
Mom.

354
00:21:04,900 --> 00:21:07,133
Even going outside the house,
she doesn't want to.

355
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:11,533
I called Dr. Richard.

356
00:21:12,767 --> 00:21:15,067
I asked him if he can refer
a psychologist

357
00:21:15,200 --> 00:21:16,767
who can talk to Coleen.

358
00:21:40,233 --> 00:21:40,833
Bro.

359
00:21:41,167 --> 00:21:42,067
Yes?

360
00:21:42,833 --> 00:21:45,933
You really didn't see what
happened before Jessica got hit?

361
00:21:46,733 --> 00:21:48,833
No one saw it, Bro.

362
00:21:51,167 --> 00:21:54,733
Wait, are you doubting Coleen?

363
00:21:56,533 --> 00:21:57,467
No, Bro.

364
00:21:59,900 --> 00:22:00,867
I don't know.

365
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:02,400
I'm confused.

366
00:22:03,567 --> 00:22:05,667
Bro, I feel stuck
between my two kids.

367
00:22:06,967 --> 00:22:09,733
Of course, I want Jessica
to get justice.

368
00:22:10,433 --> 00:22:13,433
But then there's Hazel,
pinning it on Coleen.

369
00:22:15,867 --> 00:22:19,067
Honestly, Bro, I believe
what Coleen says.

370
00:22:20,433 --> 00:22:23,667
But what if suddenly
some evidence shows up,

371
00:22:23,800 --> 00:22:25,200
or someone testifies?

372
00:22:26,400 --> 00:22:31,000
Coleen said they were
just tussling.

373
00:22:31,133 --> 00:22:34,533
Then she let go of Jessica.

374
00:22:36,500 --> 00:22:38,067
What if someone saw it

375
00:22:38,200 --> 00:22:40,667
and says it looked like
she pushed her?

376
00:22:41,700 --> 00:22:43,767
Bro, that's exactly
what Coleen said.

377
00:22:46,067 --> 00:22:47,200
If that happens...

378
00:22:48,000 --> 00:22:50,333
Coleen might disappear
from my life, too.

379
00:23:08,400 --> 00:23:09,267
Friend...

380
00:23:10,200 --> 00:23:11,133
Coleen is trending.

381
00:23:15,733 --> 00:23:19,400
People are claiming
they saw her push Jessica.

382
00:23:21,633 --> 00:23:26,133
But when I checked,
most of those profiles are new.

383
00:23:26,300 --> 00:23:27,600
Clearly trolls.

384
00:23:33,033 --> 00:23:34,967
I'm going to respond
to them one by one.

385
00:23:36,567 --> 00:23:37,267
Who knows?

386
00:23:38,600 --> 00:23:40,467
Maybe someone is telling
the truth.

387
00:23:41,700 --> 00:23:42,633
Friend...

388
00:23:43,667 --> 00:23:45,400
I need you to be honest with me.

389
00:23:46,233 --> 00:23:50,200
Is this pursuit of Coleen
part of your revenge

390
00:23:50,333 --> 00:23:51,000
against Felma?

391
00:23:52,533 --> 00:23:54,533
I'd be lying if I said it's not.

392
00:23:56,567 --> 00:23:57,767
But deep in my heart...

393
00:23:59,600 --> 00:24:04,267
I can feel that Coleen
really pushed Jessica.

394
00:24:05,967 --> 00:24:10,233
I won't stop until I prove it.

395
00:24:12,300 --> 00:24:16,333
And when I do,
they'd better watch out.

396
00:24:16,467 --> 00:24:20,267
All of them,
especially Felma.

397
00:24:21,100 --> 00:24:23,167
Why involve Felma?

398
00:24:23,300 --> 00:24:24,667
What did she ever do?

399
00:24:25,667 --> 00:24:27,133
Because she gave birth
to the person

400
00:24:27,267 --> 00:24:28,300
who killed my daughter.

401
00:24:30,100 --> 00:24:31,933
That is her biggest crime.

402
00:24:33,200 --> 00:24:35,467
I don't think that's right
anymore.

403
00:24:45,200 --> 00:24:46,000
Yes, Manuel?

404
00:24:52,400 --> 00:24:53,600
What do you want to talk about?

405
00:24:53,733 --> 00:24:54,667
We need to talk about

406
00:24:54,800 --> 00:24:55,367
what you're doing to Coleen
on social media.

407
00:24:55,500 --> 00:24:56,800
I'm not attacking her.

408
00:24:56,933 --> 00:24:59,567
I'm just looking for someone
who can help bring justice

409
00:24:59,700 --> 00:25:00,667
for Jessica.

410
00:25:00,800 --> 00:25:02,067
You just want to hurt Felma.

411
00:25:02,233 --> 00:25:03,300
And you're using Coleen
to do it.

412
00:25:03,433 --> 00:25:05,900
She's not the one
who killed Jessica!

413
00:25:06,033 --> 00:25:06,633
Coleen!

414
00:25:06,767 --> 00:25:07,900
- Jessica!
- Sweetie!

415
00:25:08,033 --> 00:25:09,533
Maybe Hazel is right.

416
00:25:09,667 --> 00:25:10,867
Maybe I pushed Jessica myself.

417
00:25:11,000 --> 00:25:11,767
Admit it.

418
00:25:11,900 --> 00:25:14,067
That conversation
is going nowhere.

419
00:25:14,200 --> 00:25:15,667
Take your father home.

420
00:25:15,800 --> 00:25:19,333
If you truly believe
Coleen is innocent,

421
00:25:19,467 --> 00:25:21,500
if you have no doubt at all,

422
00:25:21,633 --> 00:25:24,200
swear it, right there
at our daughter's grave.
